HOUSE RESOLUTION 170
By Howell
A RESOLUTION to commend Sophia Brenn Myers for exemplary
service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, the members of this legislative body are pleased to
recognize certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the
betterment of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Sophia Brenn Myers is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in
her role as a legislative intern for Representative Dan Howell; Ms. Myers's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, born and raised in Greene County, Sophia Myers was instilled with the
values of justice, fairness, and civic responsibility at an early age, shaping her character, career
aspirations, and overall future; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Myers was initially exposed to politics and public service when her
grandmother ran for county commissioner, a role she was reelected to several times and has
served in for twelve consecutive years; and
WHEREAS, Sophia Myers is a 2023 graduate of South Greene High School, where she
was a member of National Honor Society and FCA; the highlight of her high school career was
her participation with Greene County Youth Leadership, which provided her with the opportunity
to help her community while learning about her county's leadership, laws, and politics; and
WHEREAS, a student at East Tennessee State University (ETSU), where she is highly
regarded by her peers, Ms. Myers has achieved academic success while pursuing a Bachelor of
Arts degree in Political Science; and
HR0170
014989
- 1 -

WHEREAS, upon graduating from ETSU, Ms. Myers plans to attend law school to obtain
her law degree and become a family attorney, further demonstrating her commitment to serving
the public and upholding the law; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Myers is an adept and diligent professional and has served Animals
West Veterinary Hospital with acumen and alacrity as office manager since 2024, overseeing
billing, customer service, and organizational duties; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Sophia Myers brought her many
abilities and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred
Fourteenth General Assembly; and
WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Ms. Myers has surpassed all
criteria that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Sophia Myers has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight and
rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we commend
Sophia Brenn Myers for outstanding service as a legislative intern for Representative Dan
Howell and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
